<date>1621631408631<//date>< Text>
Overall I think this is a 3 star restaurant, however this experience makes for a 1 star review. Every fast-food place has handed out old fries at one time or another, but this place gets the award for OLDEST fries given to a customer. The fries were so old they weren't even edible, they could not be chewed. Having previously  worked in the fastfood industry myself I know how long it takes for fries to reach this state, and that is ridiculous and unacceptible. Looks like I will be ordering my fries without salt from now on and I recommend others to do this as well, as that is the only way to guarantee fresh fries. Do better Sonic, you have lowered the bar.< /Text>

< Review>
Drinks decently priced and karaoke is usually fun. But the bartenders have major attitudes and only cater to their friends. Karaoke is a jukebox set up so you pay a dollar per song you choose. Everyone puts their songs on the queue but the bartenders and their friends put their songs up first. So they skip and delete songs from all of the other paying customers. Resulting in customers leaving or not being able to sing at all because the place closes before they get a chance to. Definitely a waste of money. I would score lower, but i gave 2 stars because I've had a good time on a couple occasions and because the price of the alcohol.< /Review>

<Rating>2</Rating>< Review>
Updated Review: Previous one below was 5-stars from Aug 2015.. However, after returning and learning the bar is under new ownership you could definitely tell. Different vibe. No one doing karaoke. Unfortunately have no interest in returning. Really disappointed as it was a quaint little spot before. :(

Absolute dive bar. It's awesome. Came in on a Friday night and was greeted by the sound of Bon Jovi's "Living On A Prayer" being sung by a 22 year old female. Small space - probably only seats about 28-35 total? Anything over 30 would be pushing it. There is a pool table and the whole bar has a very opiate den vibe to it. Chill place. Normal priced beverages. Didn't see any liquor, which I have been discovering is more common in California than I expected. I think everything is done with rice wine or some sort of variant. Stick to the beer. Sad I didn't get to try the pizza as they closed before we got there.</Review>

Fix Auto  Claims to have aligned my car twice and repaired the front of my car after a minor collision. My car began making sounds after the repair and I did not want them to come near my car ever again.
From the moment I took my car over to International I was listened, to I was understood, I was heard, and I was helped.
The individuals who interacted with me most were the business owner Javier, Jesse and Evie at the front desk.
Not once did I ever have a situation where I felt dismissed or blown off or misunderstood. I was very particular about the repairs that had been done and not done on my car and International went above and beyond to make sure that everything was done according to my satisfaction.  My car had suffered severe misalignment in replacing of the parts and when everyone else was trying to tell me that it was OK and everything had been done right, Jesse and Javier believed me, advocated for me, and made great efforts to make sure I was happy with the work that was done.
Even more extremely helpful is the fact that they have a relationship with the Enterprise rental which is in the exact same office as their auto body shop so nobody ever has to worry about how to get home!
This business advocated for me, listen to me cry, yell, throw multiple sets and never once made me feel badd about the concerns I had and met and exceeded my expectations in getting my car back to where it needed to be.
I cannot say enough good things about Jesse and Javier... This location is also very family friendly as well... If you are a USAA client,  Make sure to request this shop because  they will treat your car like it's their very own!
I will be getting a spoiler installed on my car here shortly and I'm relieved to know that now I have a place to go that can do it and I will have to worry about a single thing!!!
Thank you Jesse and Javier and to the folks that worked on my car behind the scenes that put so much effort into making sure it was finally done right I owe you so much gratitude and gratefulness. < text>
I like Del Taco in general, but it is frustrating when quality differs between locations. Thankfully I can report, this location definitely did not disappoint.  The place was clean, the worker was very friendly (and since it was late and thus not crowded, even brought our orders over to the table), and most importantly the food was PERFECT.  Now how often can you say that when going to a fast food restaurant?!

Unfortunately for us this location is about a half hour even when the traffic is good.  But nonetheless, I have to say our first visit was excellent.  And whenever we find ourselves in the Roseville area again, we'll be sure to make it the first of many!</text>

< Text>
Food itself was eadible and we didn't get sick from it, so I suppose that's good. However, it was very greasy (moreso than other taquerias), bland and lacked complexity in it's flavor. Better than other fast food taco chains, but still a fast food taco chain, so don't expect much. It was the only place around to grab something quick out our way to Tahoe and went in with low expectations (the place being a fast food chain and all), so we weren't disappointed. You get what you pay for... "Authentic" Mexican food it isn't, but it's fast, cheap and clean. Oh, no public restroom there.<//Text>
